modules.description: This module defines configuration options for customizing the HTML output of components like tables, text blocks, rows, and columns. It allows setting CSS classes and HTML attributes for each element type, enabling precise control over styling and behavior in the rendered HTML. For example, it can assign specific classes to tables or add attributes to text containers to control layout or interactivity.

This module renders structured boxes into HTML, supporting custom extensions and styling through a configuration interface. It handles data types like `PrintBox.t` and `Html_types.li_content_fun`, allowing direct embedding of HTML elements and defining CSS classes or attributes for precise output control. Concrete use cases include generating styled HTML tables, text blocks, and interactive components with backend-specific extensions.
